I"C<h3 id="sharpen">Sharpen</h3>

<p>Sharpen the provided images with the techniques listed below. Be sure you <span class="command">Convert for Smart Filters</span> at the outset.</p>

<h4 id="smart-sharpen">Smart Sharpen</h4>

<p><img class="size100" alt="exercise-sharpen-smart-sharpen" src="/images/photoshop-sharpen-and-blur/exercise-sharpen-smart-sharpen.jpg" /></p>

<h4 id="sharpen-with-high-pass">Sharpen with High Pass</h4>

<p><img class="size100" alt="exercise-sharpen-smart-sharpen" src="/images/photoshop-sharpen-and-blur/exercise-sharpen-high-pass.jpg" /></p>

<h4 id="unsharp-mask">Unsharp Mask</h4>

<p><img class="size100" alt="exercise-sharpen-unsharp-mask" src="/images/photoshop-sharpen-and-blur/exercise-sharpen-unsharp-mask.jpg" /></p>

<h4 id="shake-reduction">Shake Reduction</h4>

<p><img class="size100" alt="exercise-sharpen-shake-reduction" src="/images/photoshop-sharpen-and-blur/exercise-sharpen-shake-reduction.jpg" /></p>

<h3 id="blurs">Blurs</h3>

<p>Apply blurs from the Blur Gallery as shown below. Be sure you <span class="command">Convert for Smart Filters</span> at the outset.</p>

<h4 id="field-blur">Field Blur</h4>

<p><img class="size100" alt="exercise-blur-field-blur" src="/images/photoshop-sharpen-and-blur/exercise-blur-field-blur.jpg" /></p>

<h4 id="iris-blur">Iris Blur</h4>

<p><img class="size100" alt="exercise-blur-iris-blur" src="/images/photoshop-sharpen-and-blur/exercise-blur-iris-blur.jpg" /></p>

<h4 id="spin-blur">Spin Blur</h4>

<p><img class="size100" alt="exercise-blur-spin-blur" src="/images/photoshop-sharpen-and-blur/exercise-blur-spin-blur.jpg" /></p>

<p>Once you’ve used the Spin Blur filter, you’ll need to paint out regions on the filter’s mask. You want to make sure you don’t blur the fender or the ground.</p>

<h4 id="tilt-shift-blur">Tilt Shift Blur</h4>

